CVE check: no new HIGH-severity CVE (only pre-existing Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions
           finding, tracked at project level — not introduced by 031)

Design decisions:
  1. Dataverse abstraction: IDataverseService (composite via IGenericEntityService —
     RetrieveAsync + RetrieveMultipleAsync(QueryExpression)). No direct
     IOrganizationService injection per task brief.
  2. Coordination with task 032: defined IIdentityOrganizationResolver in this
     task (031) as the coordination seam; 032's OrganizationMembershipResolver
     implements both IOrganizationMembershipResolver (canonical) and
     IIdentityOrganizationResolver (the seam). IdentityNormalizationService
     consumes IEnumerable<IIdentityOrganizationResolver> so zero registered
     resolvers is acceptable (returns empty OrganizationIds list).
  3. Per-path failure isolation: each of the 6 identity components is wrapped
     in try/catch. Cancellation is re-thrown explicitly (not swallowed). Cache
     read/write failures are fail-open (re-resolve from Dataverse — no functional
     impact). Other failures log Warning + populate null/empty for that field
     while letting other paths complete.
  4. PersonIdentity shape: positional-with-defaults so it remains compatible
     with task 032's placeholder constructor (`new PersonIdentity(systemUserId)`)
     while supporting the full record (`new PersonIdentity(id, contactId, email,
     teams, bu, account, orgs)`). TeamIds + OrganizationIds default to empty
     arrays via init-only overrides — consumers never observe null collections.
  5. Cache key: `membership:identity:{systemUserId:D}` — `membership:` namespace
     prefix aligns with the Phase 2 invalidation channel (FR-2P2.8 — task 086).

Integration test (AC-1A.4): SKIPPED per task brief — deferred to P4 wrap-up
                            manual UAT against spaarkedev1 (depends on real
                            azureactivedirectoryobjectid values + at least one
